derivation.yuyuan_name: Old English wendan 'to turn, depart', of Germanic origin; related to Dutch and German wenden, also to wind

entry.tran: (尤指缓慢、悠闲或小心地)走，行，去，往
entry.def: If you wend your way in a particular direction, you walk, especially slowly, casually, or carefully, in that direction.

example.ex: Sleepy-eyed commuters were wending their way to work.
example.tran: 睡眼惺忪的通勤族拖着沉重的步子上班去。
